## About me

Hi all! I'm a QA engineer with 2 years of testing experience in fintech.

In my last job I was responsible for several projects. I tested the Andriod mobile app. I prepared test cases' creation workflow for the QA team. I got an experience in CRM testing and web testing. I created thousands of test cases and ran hundreds of regression tests.

Now I want to improve my quality assurance skills not only in manual but in automated testing. I'm studying JS and learning the Cypress testing framework. 

And I'm open to new job offers. I'm inspired and motivated by the opportunity to test applications that hundreds and thousands of people will use every day. And participate in the creation of a quality product that brings real value.

I’m confident that I’ll find an approach to any task. What I don’t know yet, I will study (with enthusiasm! because I do like what I do).
